00:12:05.058 --> 00:12:07.394 position:50% align:center
[NATSUSA] C'mon dude. You'd
better not draw anything nasty!

00:12:07.477 --> 00:12:10.480 position:50% align:center
Relax, I'm already
finished with my artwork.

00:12:10.563 --> 00:12:12.315 position:50% align:center
Et voila.

00:12:12.399 --> 00:12:15.193 position:50% align:center
[NATSUSA] This better not
be permanent ink!

00:12:17.278 --> 00:12:18.738 position:50% align:center
[YASUNARI]
Whatcha got there?

00:12:18.822 --> 00:12:20.281 position:50% align:center
Oh. Some dinner.

00:12:20.365 --> 00:12:23.034 position:50% align:center
I figured he must be
starving for a bite to eat.

00:12:23.118 --> 00:12:25.954 position:50% align:center
But I'm waiting for the room
to clear out a bit first.

00:12:26.037 --> 00:12:31.042 position:50% align:center
That might take a while. Just
force your way in. Right? Easy.

00:12:31.126 --> 00:12:33.253 position:50% align:center
Yeah. Besides, it's about time

00:12:33.336 --> 00:12:35.922 position:50% align:center
for the first group
to say their goodbyes.

00:12:36.006 --> 00:12:39.342 position:50% align:center
The Kansai kids and the
third years are next on deck.

00:12:39.426 --> 00:12:40.885 position:50% align:center
It's really touching how much

00:12:40.969 --> 00:12:43.304 position:50% align:center
everyone here
appreciates Natsusa.

00:12:43.388 --> 00:12:46.057 position:50% align:center
We're a big team.
But it doesn't feel like it.

00:12:46.141 --> 00:12:51.187 position:50% align:center
No one's ever left out when he's
around. I wish I could do that.

00:12:52.230 --> 00:12:54.274 position:50% align:center
What did you end up making?

00:12:54.357 --> 00:12:58.194 position:50% align:center
Oh. Take a look! It's a pot of
my special stew! I added lots

00:12:58.278 --> 00:13:01.281 position:50% align:center
of fish, some protein,
a bunch of medicinal herbs.

00:13:01.364 --> 00:13:04.617 position:50% align:center
And fish cakes!
Delicious and nutritious!

00:13:04.701 --> 00:13:05.869 position:50% align:center
[YASUNARI, IKUTO]
Yum, yum.

00:13:05.952 --> 00:13:08.872 position:50% align:center
[FUUGA gasping]

00:13:11.124 --> 00:13:13.793 position:50% align:center
My skin feels raw.
Did ya get it?

00:13:13.877 --> 00:13:16.796 position:50% align:center
[YASUNARI] Most of it.
But your head's all red now.

00:13:16.880 --> 00:13:19.632 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I bet. Man, this sucks.

00:13:19.716 --> 00:13:21.968 position:50% align:center
I dunno what that stuff was
they forced me to eat,

00:13:22.052 --> 00:13:25.513 position:50% align:center
but I think my tongue's
starting to go numb.

00:13:25.597 --> 00:13:28.767 position:50% align:center
Why didn't anyone try to
stop him from bringing it?

00:13:28.850 --> 00:13:35.315 position:50% align:center
I'm so sorry. None of us had any
idea what Yuu was capable of.

00:13:35.398 --> 00:13:36.775 position:50% align:center
You've been wearing
that ice pack

00:13:36.858 --> 00:13:39.444 position:50% align:center
for about 20 minutes, I think.

00:13:39.527 --> 00:13:41.571 position:50% align:center
We should swap it
with something warm.

00:13:41.654 --> 00:13:44.783 position:50% align:center
Hidaka brought a hot pad.
I'll go heat it up.

00:13:50.789 --> 00:13:52.457 position:50% align:center
[YUU]
Hi, Tsuru!

00:13:52.540 --> 00:13:54.250 position:50% align:center
You're still here?

00:13:54.334 --> 00:13:56.169 position:50% align:center
[YUU]
There was some leftover food.

00:13:56.252 --> 00:13:57.837 position:50% align:center
I was packing it away.

00:13:57.921 --> 00:14:00.965 position:50% align:center
Tomorrow I can use it
to make porridge rice!

00:14:01.049 --> 00:14:02.926 position:50% align:center
Sounds great, man.

00:14:03.009 --> 00:14:08.014 position:50% align:center
Anyway, I wanted to apologize.
I had a rough time today.

00:14:08.098 --> 00:14:12.018 position:50% align:center
I'm sure you'll get better
at taping me. No big deal.

00:14:12.102 --> 00:14:15.772 position:50% align:center
But I'm no Natsusa.

00:14:17.273 --> 00:14:20.068 position:50% align:center
[YUU] That guy--
he's like a magician.

00:14:20.151 --> 00:14:23.571 position:50% align:center
A one-man wonder who
can do everything.

00:14:23.655 --> 00:14:27.534 position:50% align:center
Meanwhile, I can barely
finish a single chore.

00:14:27.617 --> 00:14:29.577 position:50% align:center
Let alone juggle all of them.

00:14:29.661 --> 00:14:30.954 position:50% align:center
Hold on.

00:14:31.037 --> 00:14:33.623 position:50% align:center
There's plenty of stuff that
you can do and he can't.

00:14:33.707 --> 00:14:34.874 position:50% align:center
[YUU]
Huh?

00:14:34.958 --> 00:14:37.919 position:50% align:center
You handle the budget,
manage the inventory,

00:14:38.003 --> 00:14:40.463 position:50% align:center
and update our website, too.

00:14:40.547 --> 00:14:42.007 position:50% align:center
You even made that app.

00:14:42.090 --> 00:14:45.468 position:50% align:center
If you're slow, it's 'cause
you don't cut corners.

00:14:45.552 --> 00:14:47.512 position:50% align:center
That's how rugby works.

00:14:47.595 --> 00:14:49.973 position:50% align:center
Each of us depends on
our fellow teammates,

00:14:50.056 --> 00:14:52.559 position:50% align:center
and we make up for each
other's weaknesses.

00:14:52.642 --> 00:14:56.271 position:50% align:center
There's no other way for a
team to realize its potential.

00:14:56.354 --> 00:14:58.481 position:50% align:center
I bet it's the same
for managers.

00:14:58.565 --> 00:15:02.902 position:50% align:center
We can only do our best.
No more than that.

00:15:05.071 --> 00:15:07.657 position:50% align:center
Hey, why'd you start
crying all of a sudden?

00:15:07.741 --> 00:15:11.703 position:50% align:center
[YUU] Sorry. Bad habit.
You know something?

00:15:11.786 --> 00:15:15.832 position:50% align:center
When I became a manager,
I felt this relief.

00:15:15.915 --> 00:15:18.835 position:50% align:center
Like I finally found
my true calling.

00:15:18.918 --> 00:15:24.132 position:50% align:center
And then, I was a mess today.
Making trouble for everyone.

00:15:24.215 --> 00:15:28.011 position:50% align:center
Big help I was.
I thought I was finished.

00:15:28.094 --> 00:15:32.807 position:50% align:center
Tsuru, you helped me to
realize I'm where I belong.

00:15:32.891 --> 00:15:34.601 position:50% align:center
[YASUNARI]
Yasunari.

00:15:34.684 --> 00:15:39.022 position:50% align:center
That's what you should call me.
Nobody uses my last name anyway.

00:15:39.105 --> 00:15:43.193 position:50% align:center
And, uh, I guess since
you and I are cool now...

00:15:43.276 --> 00:15:44.778 position:50% align:center
Sure!

00:15:46.237 --> 00:15:48.281 position:50% align:center
Hey, what're you doing
crying out here?

00:15:48.365 --> 00:15:52.160 position:50% align:center
No matter how slow the years go,
the little ones grow up so fast.

00:15:52.243 --> 00:15:54.412 position:50% align:center
What is this, a holiday special?

00:15:55.455 --> 00:15:57.874 position:50% align:center
So tingly.

00:15:57.957 --> 00:15:59.459 position:50% align:center
Hey, Yasunari.

00:15:59.542 --> 00:16:03.171 position:50% align:center
My tongue is still--
Huh, oh, you again?

00:16:03.254 --> 00:16:04.673 position:50% align:center
You doin' okay?

00:16:04.756 --> 00:16:08.843 position:50% align:center
Better than this afternoon.
Why the long face?

00:16:08.927 --> 00:16:13.807 position:50% align:center
[sighs] So, why the red face?

00:16:14.808 --> 00:16:17.519 position:50% align:center
[NATSUSA] Oh, The guys thought
up some "alternative" medicines

00:16:17.602 --> 00:16:18.645 position:50% align:center
to use on me.

00:16:18.728 --> 00:16:22.273 position:50% align:center
It sure beats people
leaving you alone.

00:16:22.357 --> 00:16:24.609 position:50% align:center
Did Taisei visit you today?

00:16:24.693 --> 00:16:27.445 position:50% align:center
Now that you mention it,
I haven't seen him at all.

00:16:27.529 --> 00:16:29.280 position:50% align:center
No kidding.

00:16:32.200 --> 00:16:34.327 position:50% align:center
[NATSUSA]
Hey, Ibuki.

00:16:34.411 --> 00:16:37.330 position:50% align:center
I want you to come over here and
look up at the ceiling with me.

00:16:37.414 --> 00:16:39.582 position:50% align:center
--Huh?
--Just do it.

00:16:41.876 --> 00:16:43.169 position:50% align:center
Nice view.

00:16:43.253 --> 00:16:47.424 position:50% align:center
You gotta press this
button for the full effect.

00:16:47.507 --> 00:16:52.012 position:50% align:center
[MOKA] Don't be a sourpuss.
You cheer up right meow!

00:16:52.095 --> 00:16:53.638 position:50% align:center
Ya feel better yet?

00:16:53.722 --> 00:16:55.765 position:50% align:center
No. I'm too distracted by

00:16:55.849 --> 00:16:57.892 position:50% align:center
whatever weird smell
ya got goin' on.

00:16:57.976 --> 00:16:59.686 position:50% align:center
That would the
delicious cake stew

00:16:59.769 --> 00:17:01.521 position:50% align:center
that Yuu made for me.

00:17:01.604 --> 00:17:03.857 position:50% align:center
Tasty. It kinda smells
like somebody

00:17:03.940 --> 00:17:05.984 position:50% align:center
mixed moldy leftovers
with bleach.

00:17:06.067 --> 00:17:08.778 position:50% align:center
I didn't wanna be rude,
so I ended up eating it all.

00:17:08.862 --> 00:17:11.072 position:50% align:center
Super gross, not gonna lie.

00:17:11.156 --> 00:17:14.826 position:50% align:center
Wait. Where has Sei been all day
if he's not here with you?

00:17:14.909 --> 00:17:17.787 position:50% align:center
Oh, good point.
I haven't seen him.

00:17:34.929 --> 00:17:36.514 position:50% align:center
[gasps] That's right.

00:17:36.598 --> 00:17:39.142 position:50% align:center
I almost forgot to bring
the cooler from the van!

00:17:39.225 --> 00:17:40.393 position:50% align:center
[NATSUSA]
Oh! I'll run 'n grab it.

00:17:40.477 --> 00:17:43.104 position:50% align:center
No. You should just
stay here, Natsusa!

00:17:43.188 --> 00:17:44.898 position:50% align:center
[NATSUSA]
Huh. But I'm fine!

00:17:44.981 --> 00:17:48.068 position:50% align:center
[YUU] Nuh-uh. I'll do the heavy
lifting--just take it easy!

00:17:48.151 --> 00:17:49.235 position:50% align:center
Are you sure?

00:17:49.319 --> 00:17:52.113 position:50% align:center
[YUU] I've got it.
You can leave it to me!

00:17:52.197 --> 00:17:55.241 position:50% align:center
Wow, look at him.
Someone's fired up today.

00:17:55.325 --> 00:17:56.743 position:50% align:center
Yeah, he sure is.

00:17:56.826 --> 00:17:59.913 position:50% align:center
If I may, sir. I need
to go to the restroom!

00:17:59.996 --> 00:18:01.247 position:50% align:center
--[SOUSUKE] Me, too!
--[ETHAN] Me, too!

00:18:01.331 --> 00:18:04.501 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah? Then repeat after me!

00:18:04.584 --> 00:18:06.336 position:50% align:center
I promise I will not fight!

00:18:06.419 --> 00:18:08.338 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
I promise I will not fight!

00:18:08.421 --> 00:18:11.132 position:50% align:center
I will not allow my
opponent to provoke me!

00:18:11.216 --> 00:18:13.343 position:50% align:center
[GROUP] I will not allow my
opponent to provoke me!

00:18:13.426 --> 00:18:15.220 position:50% align:center
What are those guys doing?

00:18:15.303 --> 00:18:18.890 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah! When we played
against this school last year,

00:18:18.973 --> 00:18:20.892 position:50% align:center
there was a big brawl.

00:18:20.975 --> 00:18:24.437 position:50% align:center
The fighting got so bad they
almost canceled the match.

00:18:24.521 --> 00:18:25.605 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Mm-hm.

00:18:25.689 --> 00:18:27.899 position:50% align:center
An unbelievably brutish
display, indeed.

00:18:27.982 --> 00:18:30.235 position:50% align:center
[TAKUMI] That sure was
a huge load of bullcrap.

00:18:30.318 --> 00:18:31.903 position:50% align:center
You two started the whole thing!

00:18:31.986 --> 00:18:33.196 position:50% align:center
You pissed off the other team,

00:18:33.279 --> 00:18:35.031 position:50% align:center
and then they
decided to retaliate.

00:18:35.115 --> 00:18:37.450 position:50% align:center
Next thing you know,
everyone's throwing hands.

00:18:37.534 --> 00:18:39.953 position:50% align:center
I don't recall it
going like that, do you?

00:18:40.036 --> 00:18:42.914 position:50% align:center
Not at all! It was nothing
but a bit of banter!

00:18:42.997 --> 00:18:46.084 position:50% align:center
The first years are the ones who
always get picked on the most.

00:18:46.167 --> 00:18:48.336 position:50% align:center
Those two were
troublemakers, for sure.

00:18:48.420 --> 00:18:51.673 position:50% align:center
But the other freshman were more
laid back, so it balanced out.

00:18:51.756 --> 00:18:54.801 position:50% align:center
With the three of you, I don't
think we'll be as lucky.

00:18:54.884 --> 00:18:56.302 position:50% align:center
Don't worry about it.

00:18:56.386 --> 00:18:58.930 position:50% align:center
I've got two of the rowdier
hooligans under my control.

00:18:59.014 --> 00:19:00.598 position:50% align:center
I appreciate that.

00:19:00.682 --> 00:19:03.768 position:50% align:center
Someone has to keep their cool,
so I'm glad it's you.

00:19:03.852 --> 00:19:06.312 position:50% align:center
[FUUGA] Uh. Since when
am I hot-headed?

00:19:06.396 --> 00:19:08.773 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Do you need a reminder?

00:19:08.857 --> 00:19:10.817 position:50% align:center
I see Ren and Shin have
taken the initiative

00:19:10.900 --> 00:19:14.237 position:50% align:center
and restrained the other problem
child. So, let's be on our best

00:19:14.320 --> 00:19:16.239 position:50% align:center
behavior from this
moment forward.

00:19:16.322 --> 00:19:19.868 position:50% align:center
Okay. I hope you're all ready
for some good, clean fun.

00:19:19.951 --> 00:19:21.494 position:50% align:center
Don't let 'em get to you!

00:19:21.578 --> 00:19:23.371 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Yes, sir!

00:19:25.165 --> 00:19:26.416 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:19:26.499 --> 00:19:27.709 position:50% align:center
What're you looking at?

00:19:27.792 --> 00:19:28.543 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Oh, boy.

00:19:28.626 --> 00:19:29.461 position:50% align:center
Back off!

00:19:29.544 --> 00:19:30.587 position:50% align:center
Walk away.

00:19:30.670 --> 00:19:32.380 position:50% align:center
[SASA A]
Yeah, don't get too close.

00:19:32.464 --> 00:19:35.592 position:50% align:center
These guys just got their asses
handed to them by Isui,

00:19:35.675 --> 00:19:38.094 position:50% align:center
you can practically smell
the "loser" on them.

00:19:38.178 --> 00:19:41.598 position:50% align:center
Sticks and stones, dude. We both
know who's gonna win big today.

00:19:41.681 --> 00:19:43.475 position:50% align:center
Really? Cause I heard
your current lineup

00:19:43.558 --> 00:19:45.310 position:50% align:center
is the most pathetic
group of amateurs

00:19:45.393 --> 00:19:46.728 position:50% align:center
anyone's ever seen.

00:19:46.811 --> 00:19:48.605 position:50% align:center
Ha. That's a bit rich

00:19:48.688 --> 00:19:50.982 position:50% align:center
comin' from a team that's
never beaten us before!

00:19:51.066 --> 00:19:52.108 position:50% align:center
Loser!

00:19:52.192 --> 00:19:54.444 position:50% align:center
Everyone, that's enough!

00:19:55.570 --> 00:19:58.323 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO]
Get out, or I'll report you!

00:19:58.406 --> 00:20:00.033 position:50% align:center
Hey, Ueoka.

00:20:00.116 --> 00:20:03.036 position:50% align:center
I heard you stepped away
from the game for a while.

00:20:03.119 --> 00:20:04.621 position:50% align:center
Whatsa matter?

00:20:04.704 --> 00:20:07.540 position:50% align:center
Were you shook up from crashing
that bike you got from Daddy?

00:20:07.624 --> 00:20:09.626 position:50% align:center
Heh. I guess you could say so.

00:20:09.709 --> 00:20:10.794 position:50% align:center
You got some nerve!

00:20:10.877 --> 00:20:12.921 position:50% align:center
[SASA B]
What, you gonna shut me up?

00:20:13.004 --> 00:20:14.464 position:50% align:center
[SOUSUKE]
You don't have the guts!

00:20:14.547 --> 00:20:18.259 position:50% align:center
[NATSUSA] Hey. You. Why don't
you mind your own business?

00:20:18.343 --> 00:20:19.552 position:50% align:center
[GROUP gasps]

00:20:19.636 --> 00:20:23.181 position:50% align:center
Who do you jerks think
you're talking to?

00:20:23.264 --> 00:20:24.516 position:50% align:center
Knock it off!

00:20:24.599 --> 00:20:25.892 position:50% align:center
[NATSUSA grunts]

00:20:25.975 --> 00:20:29.646 position:50% align:center
I said that's enough!

00:20:29.729 --> 00:20:31.523 position:50% align:center
What the actual hell, Ibuki?

00:20:31.606 --> 00:20:34.067 position:50% align:center
If you hadn't rolled over like
that, I would of had those guys!

00:20:34.150 --> 00:20:35.402 position:50% align:center
Honestly, man.

00:20:35.485 --> 00:20:37.362 position:50% align:center
Why do you go out of your
way to be so agreeable?

00:20:37.445 --> 00:20:39.364 position:50% align:center
